description: Cover story is a reprint of Justice League of America #4 - Doom of the Star Diamond!
name: Doom of the Star Diamond

volume.name: Adventures of Spirou & Fantasio: Z Is for Zorglub

description: In part one of "Fiend of the Masquerade Festival," Batman and Robin pursue an escaped convict to a public event, only to find that he's been killed. In a place where everyone is in disguise, how will they find the killer?
name: Fiend of the Masquerade Festival Chapter 1 of 3

description: As Takeda continues to train and study the ways of the Shirai Ryu, Raiden pays Scorpion a visit... and a dangerous new threat emerges.
name: Blood Ties, Chapter Two: Scorpion's Apprentice Part 1 of 2

description: Brainwashed by the Barsburg Empire into believing he’s the evil Ayanami’s faithful servant, Teito prepares to attend Princess Ouka’s sixteenth birthday masquerade ball as her bodyguard. The Seven Ghosts are determined to “kidnap” Teito at the ball, but will their bond be strong enough to free him from Ayanami’s grasp, much less the clutches of the darker shadow lurking in the palace?
name: Vol. 14

description:
A new Alice oneshot that focuses on her romance with one-time assassin Gray Ringmarc

Former assassin Gray Ringmarc serves his master Nighmare in the Tower of Clover. Known for his mature personality and kindness to animals, Gray also has a dark side. When Alice is whisked off by an adversary, Gray’s inner darkness emerges in a fit of jealousy. Now there will be hell to pay. Can Alice tame his reptilian heart?
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Alice In the Country of Clover: The Lizard Aide

description: Natsuki Matsuda, twenty-years-old, has proudly identified as gay since age fifteen. Then Komano, nineteen-years-old, comes into his life. He's always been popular with the ladies, but he's a free-spirit who cannot be tamed -- by man or woman! This is the story of their love. Can Natsuki handle Komano's bohemian nature in the long haul or will jealousy and possessiveness get the best of him? It's the return of the sweet, sweet couple from "Apple and Honey"!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Apple and Honey: His Rose Colored Life

description:
From Kaito with Love

The Kaito Kid has vowed to steal a famous artist’s latest painting—and Conan is at the scene! But while Conan prepares to stop the theft, a man is killed under his nose. Is the Kid a thief and a murderer?

Then a small boy is the only witness to a crime, but no one can make heads or tails of his strange testimony. And Conan is distracted by his suspicions about Rachel’s new friend Eisuke, who bears an eerie resemblance to one of the Men in Black!
name: From Kaito With Love

description:
Sakurai slaves away his days as a veteran ad man…but at what cost? Although his heart was broken years ago, he hasn’t found the time (or courage) to move on. Will a mysterious young painter finally help him grow past his mistakes?

Does the Flower Blossom bursts to life with surprise friendships and new beginnings! Can two lonely men truly reach out? And will the first strokes on a fresh canvas reveal the shape of beautiful things to come... Does the Flower Blossom bursts to life with surprise friendships and new beginnings! Can two lonely men truly reach out? And will the first strokes on a fresh canvas reveal the shape of beautiful things to come?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Yoto must face his pesky personal demons if he hopes to defeat the girl who stands in the way of a special someone’s happiness! But can he simply force two very strange sisters to kiss and make up?

The Hentai Prince and the Stony Cat keeps things lively with laughter, friendship…and the most mysterious statue ever created! In an all-out battle for self-hood, is speaking your mind the surest plan?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 10: How To Overthrow A Carefree King 2
  • Chapter 11: How To Overthrow A Carefree King 3
  • Chapter 12: How To Overthrow A Carefree King 4
  • Chapter 13: How To Overthrow A Carefree King 5
  • Chapter 14: Still Tagging Along With A Hentai
  • Chapter 0: A Moonless Lost World
name: Volume 3

volume.name: The Hentai Prince and the Stony Cat

description:
Misawa, the physician, harbors an unrequited love for his friend and colleague Kazami, a surgeon. There's only one problem -- Kazami is a known ladykiller. Misawa vows never to let Kazami know how he really feels until he meets Touno, an intern who can see right through him. Soon we find that Kazami has a secret of his own. Where will this triangle lead and when will they ever find the time for love in their busy schedules? "Healing people is our job. However... Only we are the attending physicians of our hearts."

Contents

  • Medical Chart 1
  • Medical Chart 2
  • Medical Chart 3
  • Medical Chart 4
  • Last Medical Chart
  • Medical Chart 0
  • One Morning, A Murmur of the Heart
name: Vol. 1

description:
Toshinari Seki takes goofing off to new heights. Every day, on or around his school desk, he masterfully creates his own little worlds of wonder, often hidden to most of his classmates. Unfortunately for Rumi Yokoi, his neighbor at the back of their homeroom, his many games, dioramas, and projects are often way too interesting to ignore; even when they are hurting her grades.

Contains 1st Period - 15th Period & two Bonus stories.
name: Mailing It In

description:
Contains volumes 11 and 12!

Furinkan High gets a new principal with some very radical ideas about student discipline and a rather unexpected relationship with blustering upperclassman Kuno. Then, poor lovesick Ryoga finally gets a break when a magical bar of soap cures his porcine transformations. If it’s not too good to be true, then it won’t all come out in the wash.
name: Vol. 11 & 12

description:
Welcome to the land of Britannia, a picturesque country ruled by the benevolent King Lyonnesse. Or at least it was, until the king's guard assassinated him and started a full-blown Holy War! Now the king's only daughter Elizabeth must seek the aid of the dreaded warriors the Seven Deadly Sins. Wrongly framed and sent into exile, they're now the princess's only hope to free the kingdom from the grip of the villainous Holy Knights!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 38: Chance & Necessity
  • Chapter 39: A Longstanding Grudge
  • Chapter 40: Vaizel's Fighting Festival Finals
  • Chapter 41: Hair-Raising Cannon
  • Chapter 42: Demon Reactor
  • Chapter 43: A Dangerous Bet
  • Chapter 44: Countdown to Despair
  • Chapter 45: Carnival of Atrocity
  • Chapter 46: Because We're Sisters
name: Vol. 6

description: Smoak Signals concludes! Can Barry save Felicity (and himself) from the mysterious Sky Lords?
name: Smoak Signals, Part 2

deck: The Rebel Alliance are looking to defeat the Empire after the destruction of the Death Star.
description:
THE GREATEST SPACE ADVENTURE OF ALL TIME RETURNS TO MARVEL!

Luke Skywalker and the ragtag band of rebels fighting against the Galactic Empire are fresh off their biggest victory yet-the destruction of the massive battle station known as the Death Star. But the Empire's not toppled yet! Join Luke along with Princess Leia, smugglers Han Solo and Chewbacca, droids C-3PO and R2-D2 and the rest of the Rebel Alliance as they strike out for freedom against the evil forces of Darth Vader and his master, the Emperor. Written by Jason Aaron (Original Sin, Thor: God of Thunder) and with art by John Cassaday (Astonishing X-Men, Uncanny Avengers), this is the Star Wars saga as only Marvel Comics could make it!

description: Whoever takes the time these days to climb a tree in bare feet? To stop and observe the comings and goings of the birds? To play in the puddles after the rain has gone? To return a shell to the sea? The Walking Man follows a modern day Japanese business man as he strolls at random through urban Japan - often silent, usually alone - with his vivid dreams that let time stand still. Every corporate American should have a copy on their desk and, in times of stress, take two chapters, twice a day. Take a little stress out of your life and relax with The Walking Man, a little step every day. Lovingly reversed in collaboration with the creator to read left to right.
name: TPB

description:
Things are going surprisingly well in Batgirl’s new life! But nothing good ever lasts long in Gotham City – and the other yellow boot is about to drop...hard!

NOTE: Batman, Dick Grayson and Barry Allen appear on variant cover only.
name: Likeable

description: Nanites are tearing The Narrows apart! Can Red Robin stop them while the rest of the city burns?
name: The Swarm

description: With legions of Parademons on the attack, Constantine forges an alliance with Doctor Fate. But as time begins to run out, will they escape Earth-2 – or help destroy it?
name: Burn the Stage

description: The final fate of Earth-2’s Clark Kent is revealed!
name: Sacrifice

description:
The devastated Corps returns to a universe that has grown much different – and much more dangerous – in their absence. John Stewart must lead the weakened Green Lanterns against a truly demonic threat’s expanding its dark reach across the cosmos.

NOTE: Barry Allen and Hal Jordan appear on variant cover only.
name: The Dark

description:
It’s the battle you never thought you’d see, as Grayson goes toe to toe with the Midnighter!

NOTE: Barry Allen appears on variant cover only.
name: The Brains of the Operation

description:
The penultimate chapter of “The Infinitus Saga” is here as the fate of the future is decided in a battle between Justice League United and the Legion of Super-Heroes!

NOTE: Barry Allen appears on variant cover only.
name: The Infinitus Saga: Part 4 of 6

description: Klarion does a very, very bad thing. Just how evil is Klarion, and how much damage will he do? Find out in “The Swarm Abides,” when Klarion drives the devil’s car and falls into a hell of his own making.
name: The Klarvoyance

description: Harley Quinn takes center stage! The Squad’s mission to China has gone to hell – and now an army of unstable super beings is trying to murder them and anything else that stands in their way!
name: Defective, Part Two

description:
Wonderstar’s destiny is starting to become clear – and his path may lead to the end of humanity! Will Superman and Wonder Woman be able to prevent him from becoming what – or who – he’s meant to be?

NOTE: Barry Allen appears on variant cover only.
name: Dark Testament

description: Terrible times are coming for Earth-2: A refugee from Apokolips brings warnings of doom, an impatient emissary is determined to bring Superman back for her master, and Batman wonders if Terry Sloan plans to betray the world. The secret history of Superman and Batman moves toward its awful climax!
name: Generations

description: “BRAGA: THE ONCE PRINCE, NOW BASTARD” Before joining the Peaches, Braga was destined to become the greatest leader of her people. But a life changing decision proved too controversial for even her most devout followers. A former life paved on the bodies of her enemies left behind...what choice was worth losing everything? Featuring guest artist TESS FOWLER!

The War changed everyone, and not for the better. After last issue’s shocking ending made one hero a murderer, find out how far Constantine went to win, and how Amethyst lost her magic! Don’t miss the return to Gemworld!

"Dancing with the Ghosts of Whales!" Collects Nightmares and Fairy Tales (2002) #19-23. By Serena Valentino and Camilla d'Errico. This collection features "Harmony," a modern and heartbreakingly beautiful adaptation of" Sleeping Beauty," in which Gwen and Aunt Bea take a trip to San Francisco and encounter the spirit of a lovely young woman wandering the Sutro Bath ruins. Also featured is "Song of the Siren," the story of a beautiful mermaid ensnared by a sideshow charlatan and put on display in his traveling carnival, an exquisitely frightening and disturbing tale. Plus, sketches and script excerpts will be included in the collection, along with pin-ups by FSc and Crab Scrambly.
name: Dancing with the Ghosts of Whales

description:
We Are The Champions

After their Tankery victory over Anzio, the girls of Ooarai Girls' Academy move on to the semi-final match. Their next opponent is Pravda Girls' High School, the winners of last year's Tankery Nationals tournament, directly due to Nishizumi Miho's actions and her unique "style" of Tankery.

Meanwhile, the Ooarai girls learn that high stakes are on the line for this match, possibly the school itself! Against Pravda's team of high-powered and strongly-armored tanks, can Miho lead Ooarai to victory? Panzer Vor!
name: Vol. 3

description:
The dieselpunk manga sensation continues!

The Strike Witches of the 501st weren’t the first witches to take to the sky, nor would they be the last. Strike Witches: One-Winged Witches covers the story of Wilma Bishop and her adventures along the English Channel in 1942, one year prior to the Second Neuroi War. As this tale unfolds, revelations about key characters and surprising details from Strike Witches: Maidens in the Sky and Strike Witches: The Sky That Connects Us are revealed, all from the unique character perspective of Wilma Bishop.

Join Wilma, sergeant of the Isle of Wight Detachment Group and ace Strike Witch, as she shows new recruits what it takes to earn their flying stripes, not to mention how to kick some nasty Neuroi butt in the process!

Back Blurb

Not All Witches Are Aces

In humanity's fight against the alien Neuroi, it's not just the super-aces and movie stars of the 501st Joint Fighter Wing who have stories worth telling. In this volume, Sergeant Wilma Bishop--the first character ever introduced from the Strike Witches world!--is transferred to the Isle of Wight detachment. it's the sister detachment to the famous 501st, but instead of aces, the Isle of Wight is filled with awkward, insecure newbies and the walking wounded. And yet, while these "one-winged Witches" may not be ready to soar with the aces, each one has her own story to tell.
name: Vol. 1

Special bonus issue! Japan's Weekly Shonen Jump is off this week, but we're giving you a couple of bonus chapters of manga anyway! Get ready for a dark one-shot that asks the question, "What Can You Kill?" Plus, Rosario+Vampire is the next JUMP BACK title! And monthly chapters of Blue Exorcist and Seraph of the End: Vampire Reign! Enjoy!

description: In a strangely tranquil town on the Texas Gulf Coast, Abe has found a little peace. That peace is threatened by Abe’s hunch that there’s a connection between this town and a deadly threat he faced not too long ago . . .
name: Dayana

description: As a desperate scientist’s violent evolution reaches its deadly apex, an alien-and-predator battle royale erupts in the bowels of the doomed Geryon armada! Now, on a ship of killers—there can be only one survivor . . .
name: Chapter Four

volume.name: Alien vs. Predator: Fire and Stone

description:
The world has lost its connection to magic, and a new breed of vampires has been born—zompires! Still, there’s more trouble for Buffy the Vampire Slayer: a magic siphon is loose, student loans have to be paid, Willow goes walkabout, and Buffy finds herself pregnant while coming to terms with her relationship with Spike. Collects Buffy Season 9 Volume 1 and Volume 2.

Expanded sketchbook and deluxe oversized format.

Brand-new arc!
name: Volume One
